						p.ar-text In this example, we're going to use Deadeye's Laser Sights card to make Empty The Clip more effective. You can follow along below or check out an animated tutorial by using the button controls! 
						br
						p.ar-text Laser Sights is a Utility card also available in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, it increases your Aim score by 1 at the beginning of your turn. If your turn begins with a copy of Laser Sights in play, your AIM score will increase from 0 to 1. That means until end of turn, all Actions and Feats you play will get a +1 damage increase. 
						br
						p.ar-text Empty Clip is an Action card available in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, it represents your player dealing 4 damage to one of your opponents.  Empty Clip's card text says to deal 4 damage to our opponent, but by adding our +1 AIM bonus it deals 5 damage instead! Since your AIM score resets to 0 at the end of your turn, make sure to use your AIM while you can!
