						p.ar-text Let's go for a big AIM score! Be sure to check out Example 1 first if you get lost! 
						br
						p.ar-text Since our last example made good use of Laser Sights, let's just say this turn starts with a copy in play. That will make sure that our AIM starts at 1!
						br
						p.ar-text Next, let's play Spotting Targets. Spotting Targets is an Action card available in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, you get to increase your AIM score by 2 and you may draw a card afterwards. Playing this will increase our AIM score by 2. Combined with the bonus received from Laser Sights, our AIM score for this turn is now 3!
						br
						p.ar-text Let's play Trick Shot last. Trick Shot is another Action card found in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, it increases your AIM score by 1 and then deals 2 damage to any Utility. Combining the bonus from Laser Sights, Spotting Targets & Trick Shot bring our AIM score up to 4! Trick Shot's card text says that it deals 2 damage to Utility, but that's without including our AIM bonus. By adding our +4 AIM bonus, Trick Shot deals 6 damage any Utility! BOOM!
